WEBVTT

00:16.016 --> 00:17.934
CAGED CLAN BRIDGE

00:22.313 --> 00:23.815
Shinsenkyo.

00:23.898 --> 00:27.360
You are the only one who has
made it back from that island.

00:27.444 --> 00:29.821
Explain what exactly happened,

00:29.904 --> 00:32.282
Yamada Asaemon Jikka.

00:33.283 --> 00:36.161
All right, the details, huh?

00:36.244 --> 00:38.329
Well, it doesn't really matter much, but...

00:38.913 --> 00:40.874
Mind if I sit more comfortably?

00:41.541 --> 00:44.085
That's a no? Okay, okay...

00:44.919 --> 00:48.089
Let's see... Where should I start?

00:48.840 --> 00:50.592
By order of the shogun,

00:51.342 --> 00:53.595
to obtain the Elixir of Life,

00:54.179 --> 00:57.098
a group of death-row convicts,
along with us Yamada Asaemon,

00:57.182 --> 01:00.101
headed for Shinsenkyo two days ago.

01:00.685 --> 01:04.105
The convict I was assigned to
was "Killing Buddha" Horubo.

01:04.689 --> 01:08.568
Before we even landed, he was killed
aboard the ship by Aza Chobe.

01:08.651 --> 01:09.736
I figured I’d head ba...

01:10.320 --> 01:13.323
Trembling with frustration
at failing my duty,

01:13.406 --> 01:15.116
I turned back reluctantly, but...

01:15.825 --> 01:18.161
the current carried us in,
and we ended up docking.

01:18.244 --> 01:19.120
Wait!

01:19.204 --> 01:21.372
Did you set foot on the island?

01:21.456 --> 01:23.124
Well... Yes.

01:23.208 --> 01:26.628
Sixty people have gone
missing on that island.

01:26.711 --> 01:30.924
I struggled over whether
to continue my duty, but I felt

01:31.007 --> 01:34.511
it was my duty to convey a condemned
man’s final moments to his family.

01:34.594 --> 01:36.429
And after some stuff happened, I returned.

01:36.513 --> 01:39.516
Wait! You're not gonna explain
what that "stuff" was?

01:39.599 --> 01:43.353
Well, it'd be a waste of time to.

01:43.436 --> 01:45.897
We should stay away
from that island from now on.

01:46.481 --> 01:49.526
That place doesn’t belong to this world.

01:49.609 --> 01:52.487
As they say, only fools
or children poke a beehive.

01:52.570 --> 01:53.905
Y-you bastard!

01:53.988 --> 01:57.158
Are you implying the shogunate is foolish?

01:57.242 --> 01:59.285
Well, I don't know about "implying"--

01:59.369 --> 02:00.912
I apologize.

02:01.621 --> 02:04.290
This man is ill-mannered,
even by our standards.

02:04.999 --> 02:06.918
The responsibility lies
with the Yamada Clan

02:07.001 --> 02:09.921
and with me, as acting instructor.

02:10.004 --> 02:11.673
Please forgive him.

02:11.756 --> 02:13.341
Hmph! Lowering your head won’t--

02:13.424 --> 02:14.259
Hey!

02:14.342 --> 02:17.720
What is it? You don’t need
to worry about an Asaemon.

02:17.804 --> 02:20.932
D-don’t you know? He was in that incident.

02:23.226 --> 02:26.980
W-well, you must be tired
from the journey back.

02:27.063 --> 02:29.691
We’ll overlook your rudeness.

02:31.276 --> 02:35.864
Now then, I will read
the official order from the shogun.

02:35.947 --> 02:37.448
Listen carefully.

02:38.032 --> 02:41.411
"The Yamada Clan shall,
once again, travel to Shinsenkyo.

02:41.494 --> 02:44.414
You are hereby assigned to oversee
those who have landed on the island.

02:44.497 --> 02:46.666
Select new suitable candidates.

02:46.749 --> 02:49.168
Yamada Asaemon Shugen!"

04:23.012 --> 04:25.640
We samurai are just pawns after all.

04:25.723 --> 04:27.558
No matter where we go.

04:27.642 --> 04:29.686
Lives that are expendable, right?

04:30.270 --> 04:31.312
Jikka-dono!

04:31.813 --> 04:34.399
Your behavior before the shogunate earlier

04:34.482 --> 04:36.067
was rather excessive!

04:37.652 --> 04:40.321
I figured if you were there,
it’d work out somehow.

04:40.405 --> 04:42.949
And it did, didn’t it?

04:43.032 --> 04:46.119
I'm saying that even I can't overlook it!

04:46.202 --> 04:47.704
Even if you are my senior,

04:47.787 --> 04:50.498
you must observe proper samurai decorum!

04:51.291 --> 04:54.252
Oh, really? My bad.

04:55.295 --> 04:57.547
I’m acting in Eizen-dono's stead now.

04:58.548 --> 05:01.050
I can’t stain his seat in his absence.

05:01.134 --> 05:03.469
Oh? How admirable.

05:04.470 --> 05:05.680
But about these reinforcements,

05:05.763 --> 05:08.725
are there even any usable
death-row inmates left?

05:09.309 --> 05:11.019
It seems the next ones
to be sent to the island

05:11.561 --> 05:13.730
will be the Iwagakure ninja.

05:13.813 --> 05:15.231
Oh?

05:17.066 --> 05:20.570
After selecting the candidates
to be sent to the island,

05:20.653 --> 05:24.574
all the condemned criminals were
apparently killed by the Iwagakure group.

05:25.575 --> 05:29.620
Pleased, the shogun selected
four ninja present on the spot.

05:30.705 --> 05:35.710
As the leader of Iwagakure,
I’ll gladly assist the shogun.

05:36.252 --> 05:40.423
I also left something
behind on that island.

05:41.257 --> 05:43.968
Leaving it to death-row inmates
in the first place

05:44.594 --> 05:45.887
was a joke taken too far.

05:45.970 --> 05:50.099
Jikka-dono, you'll join the reinforcements
and head to the island in a few days.

05:50.183 --> 05:51.809
Wha... Huh?

05:51.893 --> 05:52.810
No way.

05:53.561 --> 05:55.938
I don’t want anything to do
with that place anymore.

05:56.022 --> 05:57.398
Jikka-dono...

06:00.526 --> 06:03.362
Eizen-dono said that no matter what,

06:03.446 --> 06:06.824
he would report the situation
by the second day.

06:06.908 --> 06:08.826
This is already the third day.

06:09.619 --> 06:10.912
And it’s not just Eizen-dono.

06:11.704 --> 06:14.832
Tenza, Kisho, Sagiri... Are they safe?

06:15.625 --> 06:17.210
When I think about them,

06:18.252 --> 06:20.463
I can't bear to just sit here and wait.

06:21.089 --> 06:24.217
Yeah. I’m worried too.

06:24.842 --> 06:25.802
That's why

06:26.302 --> 06:28.596
we should go to the island ourselves

06:28.679 --> 06:30.598
and complete the mission swiftly.

06:30.681 --> 06:31.808
E-excuse me!

06:32.809 --> 06:33.851
Samurai!

06:33.935 --> 06:36.104
What should we do with this?

06:36.187 --> 06:37.313
Huh?

06:37.396 --> 06:39.690
This... Well...

06:39.774 --> 06:43.361
I thought if I showed this,
the higher-ups would be convinced

06:43.986 --> 06:47.240
it was a dangerous island. But you know,

06:47.824 --> 06:51.994
we never got to show this off.

06:52.578 --> 06:55.373
We went out of our way to haul it up
with an anchor stuck in it too.

06:55.456 --> 06:56.958
Total waste of effort.

06:58.584 --> 07:00.586
Sorry, sorry.

07:00.670 --> 07:03.131
To make it up to you,
I’ll take you to the pleasure district.

07:03.840 --> 07:04.882
Or...

07:05.466 --> 07:07.301
you could come to my bedchamber?

07:07.385 --> 07:10.221
- Either way is fine, right?
- No, um...

07:11.139 --> 07:13.099
Don’t touch it, sir!

07:13.182 --> 07:15.143
That tentacle might still be alive!

07:15.726 --> 07:17.854
No. It’s already dead.

07:18.438 --> 07:20.106
I don’t sense the waves of life.

07:21.149 --> 07:23.359
Let's go, Jikka-dono.

07:23.860 --> 07:26.904
Waves of... life?

07:28.573 --> 07:31.868
Sorry to keep you waiting.
The report to the shogunate is finished.

07:32.660 --> 07:35.037
We’ll head to the island as planned,
just the four of us.

07:35.621 --> 07:38.040
This time, it’s a team
chosen purely by ability.

07:38.124 --> 07:39.625
Jikka-dono will come as well.

07:39.709 --> 07:43.171
Huh? I don't recall agreeing to that.

07:43.754 --> 07:45.423
We will depart immediately...

07:46.215 --> 07:47.550
for Shinsenkyo.

07:50.511 --> 07:52.930
Tao is life itself.

07:53.514 --> 07:58.436
Using Tao is equivalent
to consuming one’s own life.

07:58.519 --> 08:00.605
The more you use it, the more the body,

08:00.688 --> 08:03.274
or the soul, will suffer the effects.

08:03.357 --> 08:04.942
It will show on you.

08:05.026 --> 08:08.154
Aren’t body and soul separate?

08:08.237 --> 08:09.197
No.

08:09.780 --> 08:13.201
They’re both merely forms of Tao.

08:14.118 --> 08:15.953
You're talking about
complicated stuff again!

08:16.037 --> 08:18.206
You said you wouldn’t
do that here, didn't you?

08:19.081 --> 08:20.458
S-sorry!

08:23.169 --> 08:25.004
Just kidding!

08:25.087 --> 08:26.631
Don't bow down!

08:26.714 --> 08:28.549
Lift your head. Come on!

08:29.133 --> 08:30.843
Heads up!

08:33.471 --> 08:37.892
So, Rien? Isn't the new
training hall just wonderful?

08:38.476 --> 08:40.895
Yes. Splendid, Tao Fa.

08:41.812 --> 08:43.231
By learning different movements

08:43.314 --> 08:46.150
and breathing underwater
and on the surface,

08:46.234 --> 08:48.653
it becomes training in daoyin
and embryonic breathing.

08:48.736 --> 08:50.696
Music encourages meditation

08:50.780 --> 08:53.407
and trains you in keeping
your unity and the microcosmic orbit.

08:53.991 --> 08:57.286
That room is good too,
perfect for focusing on Bochu Jutsu.

08:57.370 --> 08:58.538
I know, right?

08:58.621 --> 08:59.914
That’s stupid.

09:00.915 --> 09:04.585
If Bochu Jutsu
are about yin-yang circulation,

09:04.669 --> 09:07.547
then it’s enough to stay
in the middle like me.

09:08.172 --> 09:09.298
That’s not true.

09:10.174 --> 09:12.468
Tao takes on individuality,
depending on the life that bears it.

09:13.386 --> 09:15.304
By mingling with others,

09:15.388 --> 09:18.224
you draw out new power in Tao.

09:28.484 --> 09:31.904
Ju Fa, you're going too far. It's awesome.

09:33.656 --> 09:36.033
You two are so dedicated to training!

09:36.617 --> 09:37.743
Want some Tan?

09:37.827 --> 09:39.161
Huh? Oh, yeah, give me one.

09:39.245 --> 09:41.664
Mu Dan made these!

09:42.290 --> 09:44.166
Freshly squeezed!

09:45.126 --> 09:46.586
Here you go.

09:47.753 --> 09:50.298
I forgot to put in the glowing one.

09:50.381 --> 09:52.425
You know, the one that makes drinks glow.

09:52.508 --> 09:54.802
Where was it again, Zhu Jin?

09:54.885 --> 09:57.138
Who knows? Beats me.

10:04.312 --> 10:06.480
We're inside of the Shinsenkyo castle.

10:07.189 --> 10:09.358
Staying in one place is dangerous.

10:09.442 --> 10:10.985
Let's take a step outside the gate.

10:11.569 --> 10:12.987
Okay.

10:13.070 --> 10:15.072
That outfit...

10:15.156 --> 10:17.366
I can’t even tell what kind
of group we are anymore.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.619
It’s fine. It’s cute.

10:20.202 --> 10:22.580
Bloodstained clothes would stand out.

10:22.663 --> 10:24.165
Just turn a blind eye to it.

10:24.248 --> 10:25.499
Just like sensei!

10:26.876 --> 10:27.752
Anyway,

10:28.294 --> 10:33.007
our immediate goal
is to reunite with Gabimaru and Mei.

10:33.758 --> 10:36.010
If Gabimaru's aim is the elixir,

10:36.093 --> 10:38.387
then this castle
is likely his destination.

10:38.471 --> 10:40.014
If we went outside the gate,

10:40.097 --> 10:41.766
it'd be better
for regrouping too, wouldn't it?

10:42.516 --> 10:43.934
Wait a second.

10:44.018 --> 10:45.895
Do we really need to regroup?

10:45.978 --> 10:49.357
Are we still even doing this whole
"get the elixir" mission thing?

10:49.440 --> 10:51.859
The island’s crawling with monsters,

10:51.942 --> 10:55.488
and there are those total
nightmare Tensen things.

10:55.571 --> 10:57.823
The mission’s basically void, right?

10:57.907 --> 11:01.410
Wouldn’t the best move be
to get the hell off the island?

11:02.953 --> 11:04.622
No. We regroup.

11:04.705 --> 11:07.958
What? I'm saying this
for your sake, my beloved Sagiri!

11:08.042 --> 11:09.919
That’s not how you really feel, is it?

11:10.961 --> 11:15.508
You started acting this way
after learning there’s no elixir.

11:15.591 --> 11:18.719
As a safety net for leaving without it,

11:18.803 --> 11:21.847
you want more Asaemon, who’ll
support us before the shogunate.

11:22.848 --> 11:24.934
You just want to help yourself, don't you?

11:26.018 --> 11:27.103
You saw through me?

11:27.186 --> 11:28.104
Even so...

11:28.687 --> 11:30.398
I still want to leave the island together.

11:30.481 --> 11:31.899
That hasn’t changed.

11:32.525 --> 11:35.486
I even find your rationality reassuring.

11:36.195 --> 11:38.572
If we leave, everyone leaves.

11:38.656 --> 11:40.991
You too. Gabimaru too.

11:42.701 --> 11:47.039
Well, there’s no guarantee
Gabimaru will make it this far.

11:48.958 --> 11:51.627
I think he already has. Probably.

11:52.336 --> 11:56.006
There was a huge burn mark
and a broken wall near the gate.

11:56.090 --> 11:58.426
Only he could leave a mark like that.

11:58.968 --> 12:02.638
If we’re regrouping,
going outside the gate is logical.

12:03.848 --> 12:05.891
Thank you very much.

12:06.475 --> 12:09.562
Once you decide something,
you won't listen to anyone else anyway.

12:10.354 --> 12:11.689
But still,

12:11.772 --> 12:14.650
if we do reunite,
what do we do about that thing?

12:15.317 --> 12:17.403
Gabimaru's wife, I mean.

12:23.742 --> 12:25.494
If we climb up here,

12:25.578 --> 12:28.289
will we really get
to the Shinsenkyo castle?

12:28.372 --> 12:30.499
I can’t see a thing.

12:30.583 --> 12:32.084
I’m not lying.

12:32.168 --> 12:35.296
Miss, you don’t need to copy
my way of speaking.

12:35.921 --> 12:38.257
Now, what should I do?

12:38.340 --> 12:39.967
My memory still hasn’t returned.

12:40.843 --> 12:44.346
From what they’re saying,
this mission is utterly absurd.

12:44.930 --> 12:48.851
Why did I even take it?
Was it just an order?

12:50.269 --> 12:52.605
Or was there some other reason?

12:54.106 --> 12:55.941
No good. I can’t remember.

12:57.526 --> 12:58.986
Are you okay?

12:59.737 --> 13:01.530
You don’t look well.

13:03.282 --> 13:04.533
It’s nothing.

13:14.335 --> 13:16.003
A human, huh?

13:16.086 --> 13:19.006
Then that makes you an ally,
situation-wise, right?

13:28.724 --> 13:30.059
This guy's good.

13:30.142 --> 13:31.685
You could just cooperate.

13:32.895 --> 13:35.940
You won’t cooperate, right?

13:47.701 --> 13:49.745
Cooperate? Pointless.

13:50.329 --> 13:51.288
That was quick.

13:51.997 --> 13:55.000
Gabimaru! That guy’s Tao is huge.

13:56.210 --> 13:58.879
It's insanely huge!

14:03.300 --> 14:05.719
Cooperate? Not interested.

14:05.803 --> 14:08.514
Didn't he snap his neck?

14:08.597 --> 14:10.808
Yes. But he healed.

14:11.934 --> 14:14.436
An immortal monster ruling the island.

14:14.520 --> 14:17.314
Is this what they were
talking about last night?

14:17.398 --> 14:19.525
Restrain him and extract information.

14:25.698 --> 14:27.908
One more.

14:29.243 --> 14:31.871
Huh? Did you laugh?

14:31.954 --> 14:34.248
You're pretty relaxed, you little shit.

14:34.331 --> 14:37.376
I’ll just break you in the end,
same as always.

14:37.459 --> 14:38.627
Easy.

14:38.711 --> 14:41.130
No need to even think too much.

14:41.213 --> 14:42.464
Ninja Art: Blooming Needles!

14:43.465 --> 14:45.342
Go for the brain...

14:49.263 --> 14:51.098
- and the eyes.
- Gah!

14:51.181 --> 14:54.476
Taking away perception
should work even on an immortal.

14:59.982 --> 15:02.151
Biting through tendons...

15:02.234 --> 15:04.904
Is that something a human does?

15:05.613 --> 15:08.449
Arteries, nerves.

15:08.532 --> 15:11.076
Pressure points. The kill point.

15:17.249 --> 15:18.584
Carotid artery.

15:18.667 --> 15:21.420
Concentrated attacks on vital points.

15:21.503 --> 15:22.671
Rational, but...

15:22.755 --> 15:24.590
It's quite a brutal way of doing it.

15:24.673 --> 15:27.343
It's like how animals fight.

15:28.469 --> 15:30.804
Doesn’t matter what the opponent is.

15:30.888 --> 15:33.557
We of Iwagakure
break things until they break.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.483
That’s it?

15:42.566 --> 15:44.735
You’re nothing special.

15:47.821 --> 15:49.239
Watch your feet!

15:52.326 --> 15:55.412
You looked strong when I saw you
on the mainland,

15:55.496 --> 15:57.456
so I let you land a few hits.

15:58.749 --> 16:01.335
But you’re weak.

16:15.474 --> 16:16.392
Huh?

16:17.726 --> 16:20.646
All you can do is be nasty.

16:21.230 --> 16:23.649
Not that I mind crudeness.

16:23.732 --> 16:26.443
Rational, but dull.

16:27.027 --> 16:29.530
You were clearly stronger before.

16:30.114 --> 16:31.907
What’s going on, miss?

16:31.991 --> 16:34.618
Did getting knocked out make him weaker?

16:34.702 --> 16:35.661
Gabimaru...

16:35.744 --> 16:38.038
Your Tao is strange.

16:40.124 --> 16:42.292
Even when I focus, it won't go away.

16:44.044 --> 16:47.047
That sense of wrongness won’t go away.

16:48.132 --> 16:50.509
You can't just be strong.

16:50.592 --> 16:54.346
You need to be both strong and weak.

16:54.430 --> 16:57.391
Weakness is the seed of strength.

16:57.474 --> 17:00.310
Gabimaru has no seed of strength.

17:00.394 --> 17:02.813
He lacks something important.

17:02.896 --> 17:06.442
This strange sense of loss...

17:20.247 --> 17:21.415
Enough, Toma!

17:21.498 --> 17:24.418
Kill the others too, all of them!

17:24.501 --> 17:26.170
Yes, brother!

17:26.253 --> 17:27.296
Brother?

17:29.548 --> 17:31.759
I’ll start with the one-armed guy.

17:31.842 --> 17:34.053
Too much muscle-cutting’s a pain.

17:37.014 --> 17:38.390
Hey, jerk.

17:38.474 --> 17:40.934
Why’d you come after me first? Huh?

17:41.018 --> 17:43.187
Because I’ve got one arm?

17:43.270 --> 17:47.191
I looked easiest to kill? Huh?

17:50.444 --> 17:52.404
Don’t underestimate me, kid.

17:57.201 --> 18:01.121
Pick it up. I’ll handle the likes of you
without even drawing my blade.

18:02.456 --> 18:04.374
Wait, Blade Dragon.

18:04.458 --> 18:07.169
He seems to have his reasons,
but he’s technically of the Yamada Clan--

18:07.252 --> 18:08.128
Shut up.

18:08.712 --> 18:12.508
Anyone who looks down on me
won’t walk away whole.

18:13.092 --> 18:16.011
This one’s sharp-eyed. And that's not all.

18:16.095 --> 18:18.180
Good instincts. Experience.

18:18.680 --> 18:21.600
Then I’ll use his reflexes against him.

18:28.357 --> 18:30.859
Great coordination and sword speed.

18:30.943 --> 18:32.194
You’ve got talent.

18:32.277 --> 18:35.572
But that’s all. No real skill.

18:35.656 --> 18:38.200
Your form and technique are sloppy.

18:38.283 --> 18:40.702
Just slashing away hastily.

18:40.786 --> 18:42.913
Don’t disrespect the proper form!

18:42.996 --> 18:47.167
Because it’s practical,
it gets refined and preserved as form.

18:47.960 --> 18:50.462
Were you resting on your talent?

18:50.546 --> 18:52.631
In real combat, you relied
on your brother, didn’t you?

18:52.714 --> 18:55.092
I can tell from that unscarred face.

18:57.177 --> 18:59.429
You could’ve begged to cooperate.

18:59.513 --> 19:01.265
You might've made me pity you.

19:01.849 --> 19:05.519
If my brother won’t cooperate,
I’ll follow him.

19:06.520 --> 19:08.105
And besides...

19:15.487 --> 19:18.615
I hate people who flock together.

19:18.699 --> 19:21.785
The bandits we led were all just pawns.

19:21.869 --> 19:23.745
I never once thought of them as comrades.

19:23.829 --> 19:27.374
The two of us,
and only the two of us, are enough alone.

19:27.457 --> 19:29.918
Don't act all high and mighty.

19:30.002 --> 19:32.838
If you’re sticking together as two,
that’s still a group.

19:33.422 --> 19:35.465
I’m a part of my brother.

19:37.259 --> 19:39.219
His grip and center of gravity changed.

19:39.303 --> 19:41.889
He’s improved just while we were talking.

19:41.972 --> 19:43.265
He’s getting better.

19:44.766 --> 19:47.769
What a stupid mindset, half-baked brat.

19:48.353 --> 19:52.524
Whether it’s stupid or not is for
my brother to decide, you old bastard.

19:53.483 --> 19:55.402
- Come help us, Doshi!
- Oh...

19:55.485 --> 19:57.362
Kill the runt and the girl!

19:57.446 --> 19:58.864
Okay!

20:03.702 --> 20:06.872
Please keep about 12 feet away.
It's dangerous.

20:13.378 --> 20:16.048
He’s tough, but I can kill him.

20:16.131 --> 20:19.801
Thanks to this Tao thing,
I can read ninja movements.

20:19.885 --> 20:22.304
And even regenerate injuries.

20:22.930 --> 20:25.390
Your Tao is exceptionally strong.

20:26.058 --> 20:28.560
Normally, you would’ve
been swallowed up by it.

20:28.644 --> 20:29.895
You haven't

20:29.978 --> 20:33.732
because it’s not something
you attained through training.

20:37.611 --> 20:41.031
He's strong. I have to focus or I'll lose.

20:41.907 --> 20:44.910
I’ll forget that uneasy feeling for now...

20:46.370 --> 20:47.579
and hollow myself out!

20:48.830 --> 20:52.501
A ninja does not simply die.
When facing death,

20:52.584 --> 20:56.922
he must inflict maximum damage
on the enemy before dying.

21:01.551 --> 21:03.303
So, that’s your trump card?

21:03.387 --> 21:08.308
But damn, you look like
you’re really suffering.

21:08.392 --> 21:12.020
A suicide move, huh? As you wish, then.

21:13.021 --> 21:14.439
I’ll kill you!

21:16.608 --> 21:18.068
Ninja Art: Fire Bridge.

21:20.153 --> 21:21.947
Ninja Art: Thunder Stones.

21:30.038 --> 21:32.165
My regeneration can’t keep up.

21:32.249 --> 21:34.167
This is bad.

21:35.752 --> 21:40.799
You plan to die with me?

21:40.882 --> 21:45.345
I don’t mind. I couldn't remember
the mission's details in the end,

21:46.680 --> 21:49.808
but even if I die, someone
from the village will just take over.

21:49.891 --> 21:53.812
Ninjas are a collective.
Individual lives have no value.

21:54.604 --> 21:56.315
I have nothing to lose.

21:56.898 --> 21:58.317
But you do.

21:59.735 --> 22:02.529
Can one who clings
to life defeat the dead?

22:04.990 --> 22:08.160
Yeah... That's right.

22:08.952 --> 22:10.287
Thanks.

22:10.912 --> 22:13.040
Normally, you would’ve
been swallowed up by it.

22:13.623 --> 22:15.751
I’ve made up my mind.

22:16.335 --> 22:20.130
I’ll release everything.

22:21.173 --> 22:23.633
I have something to lose.

22:23.717 --> 22:26.136
I don’t care if I lose anything else.

22:28.972 --> 22:30.640
That’s enough.

22:30.724 --> 22:33.977
He alone is enough for me!

22:35.479 --> 22:36.646
All right.

22:38.774 --> 22:40.108
What is that?

22:41.485 --> 22:43.945
B-brother!

22:45.280 --> 22:46.948
I am...

22:47.699 --> 22:50.077
collapsing...

22:50.660 --> 22:53.205
breaking...

24:23.211 --> 24:25.922
Subtitle translation by: Maslin Friedman
